      <p>
       At San Diego State University, careful stewardship of resources and a commitment to
                     administrative excellence form a solid foundation for our academic programs. The Division
                     of Business and Financial Affairs is committed to providing exemplary service and
                     enhancing the SDSU experience for students, faculty and the greater campus community.
      </p>
      <div aria-multiselectable="true" class="panel-group" id="accordiond17e182" role="tablist">
       <div class="panel panel-default">
        <div class="panel-heading" id="campus-heading" role="tab">
         <h3 class="panel-title">
          <a aria-controls="campus" aria-expanded="false" aria-label="Campus Services Units Accordion Heading" class="collapsed" data-parent="#accordiond17e182" data-toggle="collapse" href="#campus" role="button">
           Campus Services Units
          </a>
         </h3>
        </div>
        <div aria-labelledby="campus-heading" class="panel-collapse collapse" id="campus" role="tabpanel">
         <div class="panel-body">
          <p>
           San Diego State provides services to benefit students, faculty and staff and create
                                 a positive, enriching work environment. Units include:
          </p>
          <h4>
           <a href="/campus/logistical/">
            Logistical Services
           </a>
          </h4>
          <p>
           Logistical Services include the Copier Program, Copy Center, Electronic Recycling,
                                 Facilities Rentals, Mail Services, Material Management, Receiving and ReproGraphic
                                 Services.
          </p>
          <h4>
           <a href="/campus/facilities/">
            Facilities Management
           </a>
          </h4>
          <p>
           This group oversees the maintenance and development of SDSU University facilities,
                                 including master planning, design and construction.
          </p>
          <h4>
           <a href="https://police.sdsu.edu/divisions-operations/access-control-key-issue">
            Key Card &amp; Access Services
           </a>
          </h4>
          <p>
           This department manages campus keys and card access.
          </p>
          <h4>
           <a href="/campus/parkingtrans/">
            Parking &amp; Transportation
           </a>
          </h4>
          <p>
           Provides transportation policy and information for the campus.
          </p>
         </div>
        </div>
       </div>
       <div class="panel panel-default">
        <div class="panel-heading" id="safety-heading" role="tab">
         <h3 class="panel-title">
          <a aria-controls="safety" aria-expanded="false" aria-label="Safety Services Units Accordion Heading" class="collapsed" data-parent="#accordiond17e182" data-toggle="collapse" href="#safety" role="button">
           Safety Services Units
          </a>
         </h3>
        </div>
        <div aria-labelledby="safety-heading" class="panel-collapse collapse" id="safety" role="tabpanel">
         <div class="panel-body">
          <p>
           Safety on campus and in the workplace is a priority, and SDSU is committed to providing
                                 a safe environment for all faculty and staff through a highly trained on-campus police
                                 force, comprehensive emergency preparedness and environmental health and safety resources.
                                 Units include:
          </p>
          <h4>
           <a href="/safety/emergency/">
            Emergency Services
           </a>
          </h4>
          <p>
           SDSU Emergency Services develops, implements and maintains the university's state
                                 of emergency readiness.
          </p>
          <h4>
           <a href="/safety/ehs/">
            Environmental Health and Safety
           </a>
          </h4>
          <p>
           Works with university departments to educate, facilitate and support working with
                                 and around potential hazards on campus.
          </p>
          <h4>
           <a href="https://it.sdsu.edu/security/">
            IT Security Office
           </a>
          </h4>
          <p>
           Manages a wide range of information security services and policies to the campus community.
          </p>
          <h4>
           <a href="https://police.sdsu.edu">
            Police Services
           </a>
          </h4>
          <p>
           Protect the public through proactive law enforcement and to promote a safe and secure
                                 environment.
          </p>
          <h4>
           <a href="/safety/riskmanagement/">
            Risk Management
           </a>
          </h4>
          <p>
           Risk Management program is designed to assist with identification and management of
                                 risks to the campus, including establishment of practices that will minimize potential
                                 adverse effects.
          </p>
         </div>
        </div>
       </div>
       <div class="panel panel-default">
        <div class="panel-heading" id="hr-heading" role="tab">
         <h3 class="panel-title">
          <a aria-controls="hr" aria-expanded="false" aria-label="Human Resources Units Accordion Heading" class="collapsed" data-parent="#accordiond17e182" data-toggle="collapse" href="#hr" role="button">
           Human Resources Units
          </a>
         </h3>
        </div>
        <div aria-labelledby="hr-heading" class="panel-collapse collapse" id="hr" role="tabpanel">
         <div class="panel-body">
          <p>
           HR partners with the campus community to provide quality service and professional
                                 expertise in all areas of human resources. Units include:
          </p>
          <h4>
           <a href="/hr/jobs/" title="Job Seeker/Prospective Emplooyee">
            Jobs
           </a>
          </h4>
          <p>
           SDSU is seeking applicants with demonstrated experience and/or commitment to teaching
                                 and working effectively with individuals from diverse backgrounds and members of underrepresented
                                 groups.
          </p>
          <h4>
           <a href="https://sdsuedu.sharepoint.com/sites/BFA/HR/benefits/SitePages/Home.aspx">
            Benefits
           </a>
          </h4>
          <p>
           Employees of SDSU may be eligible for a comprehensive package of benefits including
                                 health plans, retirement plans, tuition reduction and other employee programs.
          </p>
          <h4>
           <a href="https://sdsuedu.sharepoint.com/sites/BFA/HR/CAFS/SitePages/Home.aspx">
            Celebrating Aztec Faculty and Staff
           </a>
           (CAFS)
          </h4>
          <p>
           The CAFS Committee identifies and recommends celebratory experiences to recognize
                                 the institutional and individual excellence of San Diego State faculty and staff.
          </p>
          <h4>
           <a href="https://sdsuedu.sharepoint.com/sites/BFA/HR/employment/SitePages/Home.aspx">
            Employment Services
           </a>
          </h4>
          <p>
           This program determines the appropriate classification and minimum qualifications
                                 required for staff and management positions and assign the positions the appropriate
                                 pay range.
          </p>
          <h4>
           <a href="/oerc/">
            Employee Relations and Compliance
           </a>
          </h4>
          <p>
           Advises and guides the campus community on policy and practice related to employee
                                 relations and compliance issues.
          </p>
          <h4>
           <a href="https://sdsuedu.sharepoint.com/sites/BFA/HR/payroll/SitePages/Home.aspx">
            Payroll
           </a>
          </h4>
          <p>
           The Payroll staff ensures the financial integrity of the university's faculty, staff
                                 and student compensation.
          </p>
         </div>
        </div>
       </div>
       <div class="panel panel-default">
        <div class="panel-heading" id="financial-heading" role="tab">
         <h3 class="panel-title">
          <a aria-controls="financial" aria-expanded="false" aria-label="Financial Services Units Accordion Heading" class="collapsed" data-parent="#accordiond17e182" data-toggle="collapse" href="#financial" role="button">
           Financial Services Units
          </a>
         </h3>
        </div>
        <div aria-labelledby="financial-heading" class="panel-collapse collapse" id="financial" role="tabpanel">
         <div class="panel-body">
          <p>
           The following units provide the services necessary for financial management to meet
                                 SDSU's business needs. Units include:
          </p>
          <h4>
           <a href="/financial/budget/">
            Budget
           </a>
          </h4>
          <p>
           The Budget &amp; Finance department is responsible for planning, analysis and management
                                 of the universityâs support and capital budgets.
          </p>
          <h4>
           <a href="/financial/bis/">
            Business Information Systems
           </a>
          </h4>
          <p>
           The department of Business Information Systems provides technical management and support
                                 for SDSU's financial (Oracle E-Business Suite and WebCenter Imaging) and HR (CMS PeopleSoft)
                                 administrative applications.
          </p>
          <h4>
           <a href="/financial/auditandtax/">
            Audit &amp; Tax
           </a>
          </h4>
          <p>
           The Audit &amp; Tax department coordinates audits conducted by the CSU Office of the University
                                 Auditor and other audit agencies to ensure compliance, and proper reporting.
          </p>
          <h4>
           <a href="/financial/operations/">
            Financial Operations
           </a>
          </h4>
          <p>
           The Financial Operations organization is responsible for the financial and budgetary
                                 controls and procedures of San Diego State University.
          </p>
          <h4>
           <a href="/financial/procurement/">
            Procurement &amp; Payments
           </a>
          </h4>
          <p>
           Monitors expenditures of funds administered through university accounts, ensuring
                                 all procedural requirements are met.
          </p>
          <h4>
           <a href="/financial/student/">
            Student Finances
           </a>
          </h4>
          <p>
           Provides prompt, reliable and secure service to students, faculty, staff, alumni and
                                 others who make up the campus community.
          </p>
          <h4>
           <a href="/financial/travel/">
            Travel
           </a>
          </h4>
          <p>
           Coordinates all campus policies and information related to business travel is located.
          </p>
         </div>
        </div>
       </div>
      </div>
     </div>
     <!-- End page content -->
